Bruce, I used an older 12-469, the gray and white one.  I had it
hooked up to a Behringer Xenyx 1622FX mixer along with a Shure SM58
microphone running to the computer and recorded in Audacity.  

I live in Dayton, Ohio. There there are a handful of AM stations
around.  The most prominent being 700 WLW out of Cincinnati.  The
problem I&#39;ve run into is that the stations that come in clearly start
anywhere from 2-4 bands before and after their actual frequency.

I also have a RS 20-125.  I&#39;m getting ready to do another session in a
few minutes so I&#39;ll use the 20-125.  I know it probably won&#39;t make
much of a difference as far as signal goes, but I&#39;m gonna try it out.

Jeremy








